ARTICLE 1. DEFINITIONS

1.1 "The Software" refers to the software project that adopts this
    License, including all its source code, documentation, and
    related resources.

1.2 "Personal Use" means a natural person running the Software
    on devices they own or control.

1.3 "Collective Use" means use by an organization meeting the
    conditions of Article 4.

1.4 "Cognitive Data" means notes, Agent memories, conversation
    records, behavior logs, and other data directly related to
    a user's cognitive activities produced through the Software.

1.5 "Worker-Owned Organization" means an organization that meets
    ALL of the following conditions:
    (a) Profits, after deducting reasonable collective
        operating reserves, are distributed among worker-owners;
    (b) All workers have equal voting rights;
    (c) Organizational governance is determined collectively
        by workers.

