ARTICLE 2. RIGHTS GRANTED

Subject to the terms of this License, the copyright holders
grant you the following rights:

2.1 To view, study, and research the source code of the Software.

2.2 To copy and modify the Software for personal needs.

2.3 To distribute original or modified versions of the Software,
    provided this License is included.

2.4 To run the Software for Personal Use without any restriction.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ARTICLE 3. COGNITIVE SOVEREIGNTY PROTECTION

3.1 Users' Cognitive Data is entirely owned by the individual user.
    No person or organization using the Software shall:

    (a) Collect, transmit, or store a user's Cognitive Data
        without the user's explicit consent;

    (b) Use a user's Cognitive Data to train machine learning models;

    (c) Sell, license, or otherwise transfer a user's Cognitive Data
        to third parties;

    (d) Use a user's Cognitive Data for user profiling or
        targeted advertising.

3.2 This article cannot be circumvented by modifying the Software
    or creating derivative works. Any derivative work based on
    this Software must retain this article in full.

3.3 Data processing with the user's explicit consent is not
    restricted by Article 3.1. Such consent must be voluntary,
    specific, and informed. The user may withdraw consent at
    any time, upon which the relevant data processing must
    cease immediately.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ARTICLE 4. COMMERCIAL USE

4.1 The following may use the Software for commercial purposes
    free of charge:
    (a) Individual workers (self-employed, freelancers);
    (b) Worker-Owned Organizations (as defined in 1.5);
    (c) Non-profit organizations.

4.2 Other commercial organizations must obtain a written
    commercial license from the copyright holders.

4.3 The portions of any product or service that contain code
    from this Software must be open-sourced under this License.
    Portions of the product or service that do not contain code
    from this Software are not subject to this requirement.

4.4 The copyright holders reserve the right to provide commercial
    hosting services, premium features, and technical support based
    on the Software. Pricing and terms for such services are
    determined by the copyright holders. This provision exists to
    ensure the collective's sustainable operating resources, not to
    restrict users' freedom of personal use.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ARTICLE 5. WEAK COPYLEFT

5.1 Modifications to the Software's source code must be
    released under the same license.

5.2 Applications that merely use the Software are not required
    to be released under this License and may adopt other licenses.
    "Use" herein means invoking the Software's functionality through
    its public API, command-line interface, network interface, or
    inter-process communication. Directly incorporating the
    Software's source code into another project's source code
    constitutes modification (subject to Article 5.1).

5.3 Derivative works (modifications and extensions to the
    Software itself) must be released under the same or a
    compatible license.

5.4 If the Software is provided as part of a network service,
    the source code of the Software must be made available to
    users of that service; however, other components of the
    service are not subject to this requirement.

